{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783488666636,"sessionID":"ses_0bfd0dbd6ffenhLxBpSW8JdhPn","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"call_8e134511f40f42909ecb3174","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"echo \"=== classifyLineageFailure ===\"; rg -n \"classifyLineageFailure|retryable|RETRYABLE|quota|429|auth|timeout\" .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/lib/cli-guards.cjs 2>&1 | head -30; echo \"=== deep-loop-runtime.json profile exists? ===\"; ls -la .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/assets/non_dev_ai_system/profiles/ 2>&1; echo \"=== model_profiles GLM/MiMo fallback_target ===\"; rg -n \"glm-5.2|mimo-v2.5-pro|fallback_target|quota\" .opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json 2>&1 | head -20","workdir":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public"},"output":"=== classifyLineageFailure ===\n26:  TIMEOUT: 'timeout',\n167: * @returns {{failure_class:string,retry_verdict:string,retryable:boolean,exit_code:number|null,timed_out:boolean,salvage:{salvaged:number,failed:number}|null}}\n169:function classifyLineageFailure(error) {\n188:  const retryable =\n194:    retry_verdict: retryable ? LINEAGE_RETRY_VERDICTS.TRANSIENT : LINEAGE_RETRY_VERDICTS.FATAL,\n195:    retryable,\n512:  classifyLineageFailure,\n=== deep-loop-runtime.json profile exists? ===\ntotal 16\ndrwxr-xr-x@ 3 michelkerkmeester  staff    96 Jun 30 13:36 .\ndrwxr-xr-x@ 6 michelkerkmeester  staff   192 Jun 28 22:11 ..\n-rw-r--r--@ 1 michelkerkmeester  staff  5790 Jun 30 13:36 deep-loop-runtime.json\n=== model_profiles GLM/MiMo fallback_target ===\n3:  \"description\": \"Shared small-model profile registry for cli-opencode dispatch. Each model declares one or more executor paths with their provider + quota_pool, so the fallback engine can route across pools when one is exhausted. Active small-model rotation: DeepSeek-v4-pro, Kimi-k2.7-code (Kimi For Coding plan via provider `kimi-for-coding`), MiniMax-M3 (default via the MiniMax Token Plan provider `minimax-coding-plan`; pay-per-token Direct API via provider `minimax`), MiMo-V2.5-Pro (via the Xiaomi Token Plan Europe provider `xiaomi-token-plan-ams` or Xiaomi Direct API provider `xiaomi`), GLM-5.2 (Z.AI GLM Coding Plan via provider `zai-coding-plan`). Optional unverified separate-pool stub: Claude Haiku.\",\n14:          \"quota_pool\": \"deepseek-api\",\n19:      \"primary_quota_pool\": \"deepseek-api\",\n20:      \"fallback_target\": null,\n65:          \"quota_pool\": \"kimi-for-coding\",\n70:      \"primary_quota_pool\": \"kimi-for-coding\",\n71:      \"fallback_target\": null,\n79:        \"quota_pool\": \"kimi-for-coding\",\n130:          \"quota_pool\": \"minimax-token-plan\",\n137:          \"quota_pool\": \"minimax-api\",\n142:      \"primary_quota_pool\": \"minimax-token-plan\",\n143:      \"fallback_target\": null,\n151:        \"quota_pool\": \"minimax-token-plan\",\n153:        \"notes\": \"Plain `minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M3` confirmed live (2026-06-02; re-verified on opencode 1.16.2 2026-06-06); there is NO `MiniMax-M3-highspeed` on 1.16.2. agent_policy omit-general: `--agent` is rejected on opencode 1.15.13. format_mode json: dispatch via `opencode run --format json` for the normalized token/cost/latency envelope. default_variant high is the dispatch-layer default; `--variant` forwarding for this provider was historically omitted (unverified) — confirm acceptance before relying on a non-default variant. Direct API path: provider `minimax`, quota_pool `minimax-api`.\",\n162:        \"separate quota pool (minimax-token-plan) independent of cognition and Xiaomi pools\",\n190:      \"id\": \"mimo-v2.5-pro\",\n198:          \"quota_pool\": \"xiaomi-token-plan\",\n200:          \"notes\": \"Xiaomi Token Plan (Europe) via opencode provider xiaomi-token-plan-ams (credential 'Xiaomi Token Plan (Europe)'). Live slug xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro (confirmed responsive on opencode 1.15.13, 2026-06-01); verify the full live list with 'opencode models xiaomi-token-plan-ams'. Omit --agent (warns + falls back on 1.15.13). Manual direct-provider reroute uses xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro when configured; no automatic gateway fallback is defined. Context window 1,000,000 tokens (released 2026-04-22). OpenAI-compatible endpoint https://token-plan-ams.xiaomimimo.com/v1; opencode cost shows 0/0 (Token-Plan subscription). --variant maps to MiMo reasoning effort (low/medium/high) in opencode settings — always dispatch with --variant high (confirmed accepted on opencode 1.15.13). Best prompt framework (benchmark 004, 10/10 real runs): COSTAR or RACE + lean pre-planning — frame for format/brevity, not guardrails; TIDD-EC/dense ranked last; avoid CIDI (intermittent tool-only file-writes).\"\n203:      \"primary_quota_pool\": \"xiaomi-token-plan\",\n204:      \"fallback_target\": null,\n","metadata":{"output":"=== classifyLineageFailure ===\n26:  TIMEOUT: 'timeout',\n167: * @returns {{failure_class:string,retry_verdict:string,retryable:boolean,exit_code:number|null,timed_out:boolean,salvage:{salvaged:number,failed:number}|null}}\n169:function classifyLineageFailure(error) {\n188:  const retryable =\n194:    retry_verdict: retryable ? LINEAGE_RETRY_VERDICTS.TRANSIENT : LINEAGE_RETRY_VERDICTS.FATAL,\n195:    retryable,\n512:  classifyLineageFailure,\n=== deep-loop-runtime.json profile exists? ===\ntotal 16\ndrwxr-xr-x@ 3 michelkerkmeester  staff    96 Jun 30 13:36 .\ndrwxr-xr-x@ 6 michelkerkmeester  staff   192 Jun 28 22:11 ..\n-rw-r--r--@ 1 michelkerkmeester  staff  5790 Jun 30 13:36 deep-loop-runtime.json\n=== model_profiles GLM/MiMo fallback_target ===\n3:  \"description\": \"Shared small-model profile registry for cli-opencode dispatch. Each model declares one or more executor paths with their provider + quota_pool, so the fallback engine can route across pools when one is exhausted. Active small-model rotation: DeepSeek-v4-pro, Kimi-k2.7-code (Kimi For Coding plan via provider `kimi-for-coding`), MiniMax-M3 (default via the MiniMax Token Plan provider `minimax-coding-plan`; pay-per-token Direct API via provider `minimax`), MiMo-V2.5-Pro (via the Xiaomi Token Plan Europe provider `xiaomi-token-plan-ams` or Xiaomi Direct API provider `xiaomi`), GLM-5.2 (Z.AI GLM Coding Plan via provider `zai-coding-plan`). Optional unverified separate-pool stub: Claude Haiku.\",\n14:          \"quota_pool\": \"deepseek-api\",\n19:      \"primary_quota_pool\": \"deepseek-api\",\n20:      \"fallback_target\": null,\n65:          \"quota_pool\": \"kimi-for-coding\",\n70:      \"primary_quota_pool\": \"kimi-for-coding\",\n71:      \"fallback_target\": null,\n79:        \"quota_pool\": \"kimi-for-coding\",\n130:          \"quota_pool\": \"minimax-token-plan\",\n137:          \"quota_pool\": \"minimax-api\",\n142:      \"primary_quota_pool\": \"minimax-token-plan\",\n143:      \"fallback_target\": null,\n151:        \"quota_pool\": \"minimax-token-plan\",\n153:        \"notes\": \"Plain `minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M3` confirmed live (2026-06-02; re-verified on opencode 1.16.2 2026-06-06); there is NO `MiniMax-M3-highspeed` on 1.16.2. agent_policy omit-general: `--agent` is rejected on opencode 1.15.13. format_mode json: dispatch via `opencode run --format json` for the normalized token/cost/latency envelope. default_variant high is the dispatch-layer default; `--variant` forwarding for this provider was historically omitted (unverified) — confirm acceptance before relying on a non-default variant. Direct API path: provider `minimax`, quota_pool `minimax-api`.\",\n162:        \"separate quota pool (minimax-token-plan) independent of cognition and Xiaomi pools\",\n190:      \"id\": \"mimo-v2.5-pro\",\n198:          \"quota_pool\": \"xiaomi-token-plan\",\n200:          \"notes\": \"Xiaomi Token Plan (Europe) via opencode provider xiaomi-token-plan-ams (credential 'Xiaomi Token Plan (Europe)'). Live slug xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro (confirmed responsive on opencode 1.15.13, 2026-06-01); verif