{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783489051042,"sessionID":"ses_0bfd0dbd6ffenhLxBpSW8JdhPn","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_30f49f734f744531b613c93a","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# Iteration 003 - system-spec-kit Tooling-Borrow And Reference Migration\n\n## Focus\n\nValidate child 002's Stage 3b tooling-borrow edits, the `artifact-root.cjs` re-export depth, and the advisor-corpus + named-profile migration surface in child 003.\n\n## Findings\n\n1. The four Stage 3b tooling-borrow edits are confirmed necessary and correctly scoped to child 002 (not 003), because they gate physical-move validation. All four sites verified in-tree: `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/package.json:31` (`test:council` reaches `../../deep-loop-runtime/tests/integration/council-graph-*.vitest.ts`), `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/vitest.config.ts:20` (include glob `'../deep-loop-runtime/tests/**/*.{vitest,test}.ts'`), `runtime/package.json:11` (`typecheck` via `../system-spec-kit/node_modules/.bin/tsc`), `runtime/tsconfig.json:13` (`typeRoots: [\"../system-spec-kit/node_modules/@types\"]`). [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/package.json:31] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/vitest.config.ts:20] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/package.json:11] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tsconfig.json:12-13] [SOURCE: 002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/plan.md:90-99]\n\n2. **NEW P1 — the vitest.config.ts include glob is the sole gate pulling runtime tests into system-spec-kit's council suite; a wrong glob silently drops tests rather than failing.** If `vitest.config.ts:20` resolves to zero matches after the move (e.g. off-by-one in the new `../system-deep-loop/runtime/tests/**` path), `test:council` runs fewer tests with a green exit. Stage 3b verification must assert the glob matches a NON-EMPTY test set (a test-count assertion), not merely that the path string was edited. This is the same silent-shrink failure mode the 154 precedent guarded against for reducer imports. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/vitest.config.ts:18-21]\n\n3. `artifact-root.cjs` re-export depth confirmed: today `deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/artifact-root.cjs:18` reaches `path.join(__dirname,'..','..','..','system-spec-kit',...)` (3 ups → `.opencode/skills`). After nesting, `system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop` is 4 ups from `.opencode/skills`, so the join needs a 4th `'..'`. This belongs in Stage 3b (runtime→system-spec-kit tooling-borrow family), not Stage 3a or child 003. The matching tests `artifact-root.vitest.ts` and `dependency-seams.vitest.ts` (which compute `skillsRoot = runtimeRoot/..`) need the same depth correction. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/artifact-root.cjs:17-18] [SOURCE: 002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/plan.md:90-99]\n\n4. **Advisor-corpus migration is high-risk and the plan's Stage C/D/I ordering is the correct guard.** Confirmed load-bearing hardcoded surface: `skill_advisor.py:83` (`MODE_REGISTRY_PATH = SKILLS_DIR/deep-loop-workflows/mode-registry.json`), `:349` (emits `\"skill\":\"deep-loop-workflows\"` in projection codegen), `:1925-1932` (routing-weight tables with `deep-loop-workflows` literals), `aliases.ts:109` (`MERGED_DEEP_SKILL_ID = 'deep-loop-workflows'`), `routing-registry-drift-guard.vitest.ts:26,76` (hardcoded `registryPath` AND asserts projected `skill:'deep-loop-workflows'`). The drift-guard is the safety net: it asserts the codegen maps == registry projection, so renaming the registry field WITHOUT re-running the emitter would make the guard fail loudly — which is the desired behavior. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py:83] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/scorer/aliases.ts:109] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/tests/routing-registry-drift-guard.vitest.ts:26] [SOURCE: 003-external-reference-migration/plan.md:75-87]\n\n5. **NEW — divergence-ledger `reason` prose embeds the old skill name and must update WITH the structured fields, not be left as a stale narrative.** `local-native-approved-divergences.json:30-31` pairs `nativeTop:\"deep-loop-workflows\"` with a free-text `reason` (\"deep-loop merge re-baseline: legacy deep-* skills folded into deep-loop-workflows shifted native top-1...\"). Stage I correctly says update `nativeTop`/`localTop`/`reason`/`approvedAt` together per entry — but this coupling is easy to miss because the divergence ratchet test compares structured fields, while the reason is human-readable. If only the structured field is updated, the reason text contradicts the field. Keep Stage I's \"together per entry\" as a hard rule. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/tests/parity/fixtures/local-native-approved-divergences.json:30-31] [SOURCE: 003-external-reference-migration/plan.md:101-104]\n\n6. **NEW P1 — a named benchmark PROFILE FILE is named after the old skill and carries stale internal identity fields.** `deep-improvement/assets/non_dev_ai_system/profiles/deep-loop-runtime.json` (filename = old skill name) contains `packaging_root:\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime\"` and `system_name_short:\"deep-loop-runtime\"` (lines 3,5), and `meta-loop-lane-d-packaging.vitest.ts:15` asserts on this exact filename. This is NOT a code-path reference; it is a benchmark profile FOR the runtime system, so the rename target is semantically ambiguous (`system-deep-loop.json`? `runtime.json`?). A blind residual-grep would update `packaging_root` but leave the filename `deep-loop-runtime.json`, creating a name/field inconsistency, and the lane-d test would still pass on the old filename while pointing at a renamed path. Child 002/003 must make an EXPLICIT naming decision and update filename + internal fields + the test assertion together. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/assets/non_dev_ai_system/profiles/deep-loop-runtime.json:3-5] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/meta-loop-lane-d-packaging.vitest.ts:15]\n\n## Ruled Out\n\n- Decoupling runtime's TypeScript tooling from system-spec-kit during this merge — bundling a decoupling change would make a merge failure and a decoupling failure indistinguishable (child 002's own decision; out-of-scope follow-up).\n- Dynamically pointing the advisor hot path at `mode-registry.json` to avoid codegen churn — the hardcoded projection maps are an intentional cross-skill-import-coupling avoidance (mode-registry.json:4,10-17); the drift-guard is the correct safety net, not runtime reads.\n\n## Next Focus\n\nFallback-router wiring feasibility: confirm the zero-caller state, the failure-classification gap that blocks a reliable GLM→MiMo path, and the model-id normalization the registry-vs-provider-slug mismatch requires.\n","filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/glm52-5/iterations/iteration-003.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/glm52-5/iterations/iteration-003.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/glm52-5/iterations/iteration-003.md","time":{"start":1783489051038,"end":1783489051041}},"id":"prt_f403b399b001TDFBimcuDzMHEv","sessionID":"ses_0bfd0dbd6ffenhLxBpSW8JdhPn","messageID":"msg_f403a5c2e001JnaQmA54N8MvFw"}}
